text: usage: help [command] If help is used without an argument, a list containing available commands and their required arguments will be displayed. Note! If the user is logged in and connected to a running platform the list will include all commands available for the version the platform is running. When an argument is added to the help command, information about the entered command is displayed. Return Codes Listed below are the different return codes for the help command: Code Description Code Description 0 Will be returned if the command was successful. 1 Will be returned if the command supplied in the argument does not exit.
